# Accessibility (WCAG AA Minimum)

## Color Contrast

### Text Contrast (WCAG AA)
- **Body text** (< 18px): 4.5:1 minimum
- **Large text** (≥ 18px or ≥ 14px bold): 3:1 minimum
- **UI components**: 3:1 against adjacent colors

### Testing
- Use WebAIM Contrast Checker
- Chrome DevTools Accessibility panel
- Test in both light and dark modes

### Common Mistakes
- Light gray text on white (#999 on #FFF = 2.85:1 ❌)
- Colored text without checking contrast
- Placeholder text too light

### Good Examples
- #171717 on #FFFFFF = 16.1:1 ✅
- #525252 on #FFFFFF = 7.0:1 ✅
- #737373 on #FFFFFF = 4.7:1 ✅

## Keyboard Navigation

### Tab Order
- Logical, left-to-right, top-to-bottom
- Skip to main content link
- No keyboard traps (except modals)

### Focus Indicators
- **Visible**: 2px outline minimum
- **Contrast**: 3:1 against background
- **Never remove**: Don't use `outline: none` without replacement

```css
/* Good */
:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid #0078D4;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

/* Bad */
:focus {
  outline: none; /* Never do this alone */
}
```

### Interactive Elements
- All interactive elements keyboard accessible
- Enter/Space activates buttons
- Arrow keys navigate lists/menus
- Escape closes modals/dropdowns

## Semantic HTML

### Use Proper Elements
```html
<!-- Good -->
<button>Click Me</button>
<a href="/page">Link</a>
<nav>...</nav>
<main>...</main>

<!-- Bad -->
<div onclick="...">Click Me</div>
<span class="link">Link</span>
```

### Landmarks
```html
<header>Site header</header>
<nav>Navigation</nav>
<main>Main content</main>
<aside>Sidebar</aside>
<footer>Site footer</footer>
```

### Headings
- One H1 per page
- Don't skip levels (H1 → H2 → H3, not H1 → H3)
- Use for structure, not styling

## ARIA Labels

### When to Use
- Custom components
- Icon-only buttons
- Dynamic content
- Form validation

### Examples
```html
<!-- Icon button -->
<button aria-label="Close dialog">
  <icon name="x" />
</button>

<!-- Search input -->
<input type="search" aria-label="Search products">

<!-- Live region -->
<div aria-live="polite" aria-atomic="true">
  3 new messages
</div>

<!-- Expanded state -->
<button aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="menu">
  Menu
</button>
```

### ARIA Attributes
- `aria-label`: Accessible name
- `aria-labelledby`: Reference to label element
- `aria-describedby`: Additional description
- `aria-hidden`: Hide from screen readers
- `aria-live`: Announce dynamic changes
- `aria-expanded`: Disclosure state
- `aria-controls`: Related element
- `aria-current`: Current item in set

## Forms

### Labels
```html
<!-- Good: Associated label -->
<label for="email">Email</label>
<input type="email" id="email">

<!-- Good: Wrapping label -->
<label>
  Email
  <input type="email">
</label>

<!-- Bad: No label -->
<input type="email" placeholder="Email">
```

### Required Fields
```html
<label for="name">
  Name <span aria-label="required">*</span>
</label>
<input type="text" id="name" required aria-required="true">
```

### Error Messages
```html
<label for="email">Email</label>
<input 
  type="email" 
  id="email" 
  aria-invalid="true"
  aria-describedby="email-error">
<span id="email-error" role="alert">
  Please enter a valid email
</span>
```

### Field Groups
```html
<fieldset>
  <legend>Shipping Address</legend>
  <!-- form fields -->
</fieldset>
```

## Images

### Alt Text
```html
<!-- Informative image -->
<img src="chart.png" alt="Sales increased 25% in Q4">

<!-- Decorative image -->
<img src="decoration.png" alt="" role="presentation">

<!-- Linked image -->
<a href="/products">
  <img src="logo.png" alt="View products">
</a>
```

### Complex Images
```html
<figure>
  <img src="chart.png" alt="Sales chart">
  <figcaption>
    Detailed description of chart data...
  </figcaption>
</figure>
```

## Touch Targets

### Minimum Sizes
- **Mobile/Touch**: 44px × 44px (Apple HIG)
- **Desktop/Mouse**: 32px × 32px
- **Recommended**: 48px × 48px

### Spacing
- Minimum 8px between touch targets
- Adequate padding for easy tapping

```css
/* Good */
.button {
  min-height: 44px;
  min-width: 44px;
  padding: 12px 24px;
}
```

## Motion & Animation

### Reduced Motion
```css
@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  * {
    animation-duration: 0.01ms !important;
    animation-iteration-count: 1 !important;
    transition-duration: 0.01ms !important;
  }
}
```

### Guidelines
- Animations < 5 seconds
- Provide pause/stop controls for auto-playing content
- No flashing content (> 3 flashes per second)

## Screen Readers

### Skip Links
```html
<a href="#main-content" class="skip-link">
  Skip to main content
</a>
```

### Visually Hidden
```css
.sr-only {
  position: absolute;
  width: 1px;
  height: 1px;
  padding: 0;
  margin: -1px;
  overflow: hidden;
  clip: rect(0, 0, 0, 0);
  white-space: nowrap;
  border-width: 0;
}
```

### Live Regions
```html
<!-- Polite: waits for pause -->
<div aria-live="polite">Status updated</div>

<!-- Assertive: interrupts -->
<div aria-live="assertive" role="alert">
  Error: Form submission failed
</div>
```

## Modals/Dialogs

### Focus Management
```javascript
// 1. Trap focus inside modal
// 2. Focus first interactive element
// 3. Return focus on close
```

### Markup
```html
<div role="dialog" aria-modal="true" aria-labelledby="dialog-title">
  <h2 id="dialog-title">Dialog Title</h2>
  <div>Content</div>
  <button>Close</button>
</div>
```

## Tables

### Data Tables
```html
<table>
  <caption>Sales by Region</caption>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th scope="col">Region</th>
      <th scope="col">Sales</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <th scope="row">North</th>
      <td>$1,234</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
</table>
```

## Testing Checklist

### Automated
- [ ] Run axe DevTools
- [ ] Check Lighthouse accessibility score
- [ ] Validate HTML

### Manual
- [ ] Navigate with keyboard only
- [ ] Test with screen reader (NVDA, JAWS, VoiceOver)
- [ ] Check color contrast
- [ ] Zoom to 200%
- [ ] Test with reduced motion
- [ ] Verify touch target sizes

### Screen Readers
- **Windows**: NVDA (free), JAWS
- **macOS**: VoiceOver (built-in)
- **iOS**: VoiceOver (built-in)
- **Android**: TalkBack (built-in)

## Best Practices

### Do
- Use semantic HTML
- Provide text alternatives
- Ensure keyboard access
- Maintain focus indicators
- Test with real users
- Support screen readers
- Respect user preferences
- Meet WCAG AA minimum

### Don't
- Remove focus outlines
- Use color alone
- Skip heading levels
- Ignore keyboard users
- Use divs for buttons
- Auto-play media
- Create keyboard traps
- Rely on hover only
